<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-28T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/9–2851: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The United States</hi> (<gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">GATT</hi></gloss>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-28T11:00:00+01:00">September
                                    28, 1951—11 a. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 42. <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s approval US declaration on Czech suspension by vote 24
                            for, 4 abstentions (Burma, Den, Finland, Indo), Czech against. Czech del
                            refused to accept validity decision which it claims illegal. It stated
                            Czech had not asked suspension and cld not be forced to break agreement,
                            and instead asked <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s authorize Czech,
                            under Art XXVIII, to revoke concessions granted directly to US. Said
                            Czech wld continue accord US <gloss target="#t_MFN1">MFN</gloss>
                            advantages. Chairman rules Czech must submit request as separate item on
                            which <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s cld decide whether or not to
                            act.</p>
                        <p>View foregoing suggest you proceed immed <gloss target="#t_Treas1">Treas</gloss> action re Czech imports (Gatt 43, Sept 27<note n="1" xml:id="d601fn1">Not printed.</note>).</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>